      "content": "# User Profile Retrieval Endpoint (`GET /user`)\n\n## Overview and Purpose\nThis endpoint provides authenticated users with immediate access to their core profile information. It is the definitive source for fetching essential user identity data within the system.\n\n## Authentication Requirements\n### Access Control\nAccess to this resource is strictly limited to authenticated users.\n\n#### Authorization Scheme\nThe request **must** include a valid bearer token in the `Authorization` header.\n\n## Request Specifications\n### Endpoint Path\n`/user`\n\n### HTTP Method\n`GET`\n\n### Parameters\nNo query or path parameters are accepted for this operation.\n\n## Response Details\n### Success Response (200 OK)\nUpon successful validation, the API returns a JSON object containing the user's profile attributes.\n\n#### Response Body Schema\n*   `id`: (String) The globally unique identifier for the user.\n*   `name`: (String) The user's full, displayable name.\n*   `email`: (String) The verified email address of the user.\n\n### Example Payload\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"usr_12345\",\n  \"name\": \"Jane Doe\",\n  \"email\":",
